output.crosstab_text:
For level 8 graduates of Allied health, 5 years after graduation, the industry with the highest proportion of female graduates is Education, and the median earnings of females in this industry were £38,000. The industry with the highest proportion of male graduates was Human health and social work activities and the median earnings of males in this industry were £58,800.

The biggest difference in proportions is seen in Education where the proportion of female graduates is 13.1 percentage points higher than the proportion of male graduates. The biggest difference in median earnings is seen in Human health and social work activities where the median earnings of male graduates were £23,000 higher than the median earnings of female graduates.The group with the highest earnings was Male graduates who worked in the Human health and social work activities industry (median earnings of £58,800).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of Allied health by sex, five years after graduation, male and female level 8 graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
